4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REQUIRING THE DEPARTMENT OF FISH, WILDLIFE, AND
5 PARKS TO PUBLISH AN ANNUAL PUBLIC REPORT ON HUNTING DISTRICT DATA; PROVIDING FOR THE
6 REPORT FOR THE HUNTING OF ELK, DEER, AND ANTELOPE; AND AMENDING SECTION 87-1-201,
7 MCA.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 87-1-201, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "87-1-201. Powers and duties. (1) Except as provided in subsection (13), the department shall
13 supervise all the wildlife, fish, game, game and nongame birds, waterfowl, and the game and fur-bearing
14 animals of the state and may implement voluntary programs that encourage hunting access on private lands
15 and that promote harmonious relations between landowners and the hunting public. The department possesses
16 all powers necessary to fulfill the duties prescribed by law and to bring actions in the proper courts of this state
17 for the enforcement of the fish and game laws and the rules adopted by the department.
18 (2) Except as provided in subsection (13), the department shall enforce all the laws of the state
19 regarding the protection, preservation, management, and propagation of fish, game, fur-bearing animals, and
20 game and nongame birds within the state.
21 (3) The department has the exclusive power to spend for the protection, preservation,
22 management, and propagation of fish, game, fur-bearing animals, and game and nongame birds all state funds
23 collected or acquired for that purpose, whether arising from state appropriation, licenses, fines, gifts, or
24 otherwise. Money collected or received from the sale of hunting and fishing licenses or permits, from the sale of
25 seized game or hides, from fines or damages collected for violations of the fish and game laws, or from
26 appropriations or received by the department from any other sources is under the control of the department and
27 is available for appropriation to the department.
28 (4) The department may discharge any appointee or employee of the department for cause at any
