2 (5) The department may dispose of all property owned by the state used for the protection,
3 preservation, management, and propagation of fish, game, fur-bearing animals, and game and nongame birds
4 that is of no further value or use to the state and shall turn over the proceeds from the sale to the state
5 treasurer to be credited to the fish and game account in the state special revenue fund.
6 (6) (a) The department may not issue firearms within this state to anyone except:
7 (i) wardens; and
8 (ii) other qualified employees identified, trained, and certified by the department where necessary
9 to perform assigned duties pursuant to subsection (7).
10 (b) Wardens, as authorized officers under 87-1-502, are the only department employees with the
11 authority to enforce provisions of state law or administrative rule.
12 (7) (a) Department employees may be issued a firearm as allowed in subsection (6)(a)(ii) only after
13 submitting a form of final approval as determined and approved by the department.
14 (b) Department-issued firearms may be carried by an employee other than a warden only when the
15 employee is engaged in work that requires the carrying of a firearm, as determined by the department.
16 (c) When a department-issued firearm is no longer necessary to perform an employee's required
17 duties, the employee shall return the issued firearm to secure storage in the regional office to which the
18 employee is attached.
19 (8) Except as provided in subsection (13), the department is authorized to make, promulgate, and
20 enforce reasonable rules and regulations not inconsistent with the provisions of Title 87, chapter 2, that in its
21 judgment will accomplish the purpose of chapter 2.
22 (9) The department is authorized to promulgate rules relative to tagging, possession, or
23 transportation of bear within or outside of the state.
24 (10) (a) The department shall implement programs that:
25 (i) manage wildlife, fish, game, and nongame animals in a manner that prevents the need for
26 listing under 87-5-107 or under the federal Endangered Species Act, 16 U.S.C. 1531, et seq.;
27 (ii) manage listed species, sensitive species, or a species that is a potential candidate for listing
28 under 87-5-107 or under the federal Endangered Species Act, 16 U.S.C. 1531, et seq., in a manner that assists
