1 (a) the restriction of certain hunting seasons to the use of specified hunting arms, such as the
2 establishment of special archery seasons and the special muzzleloader heritage hunting season established in
3 87-1-304;
4 (b) for human safety, the restriction of certain areas to the use of only specified hunting arms,
5 including bows and arrows, traditional handguns, and muzzleloading rifles;
6 (c) the restriction of the use of shotguns for the hunting of deer and elk pursuant to 87-6-401(1)(f);
7 (d) the regulation of migratory game bird hunting pursuant to 87-3-403; or
8 (e) the restriction of the use of rifles for bird hunting pursuant to 87-6-401(1)(g) or (1)(h).
9 (14) The department shall publish an annual public report that shows the number of licenses sold to
10 nonresidents in the previous license year for each species in which the purchase of a license or permit is
11 required. The report must also show how many licenses were issued through opportunities or programs for
12 nonresidents, such as those for the following:
13 (a) youths;
14 (b) college students;
15 (c) nonresidents who were former residents;
16 (d) nonresident licenses purchased by utilizing an outfitter preference point;
17 (e) sponsorships by a landowner, family member, or current Montana resident; or
18 (f) any other license opportunity or program for nonresidents.
19 (15) The department shall publish an annual public report that shows the data on each hunting
20 district for elk, deer, and antelope by both resident and nonresident hunters. The report must be created using
21 currently available data and must include:
22 (a) the estimated number of resident hunters, nonresident hunters, and total hunters who hunted in
23 the district;
24 (b) the estimated number of days the district was hunted by resident hunters, nonresident hunters,
25 and total hunters;
26 (c) the estimated average number of days that resident hunters, nonresident hunters, and total
27 hunters used the district per hunter; and
28 (d) the species being hunted in the district."
